Description: Sliver of flattened handle of a pottery transport amphora. Clay medium, light brown; light grey core. Rectangular stamp with probable grape cluster symbol and Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie diary Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 96, 4
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1597)
